Title: Lise Meitner and Rosalind Franklin: The Nobel Prize as a Gauge for Female Scientific Achievement
Description: An analysis of the Nobel Prize system and its current male prejudices resulting from the awarding process and other societal factors. This analysis uses the lives of Rosalind Franklind and Lise Meitner as case studies.
Contributors: Julie Logan
Tags: STS, women in science, Nobel Prizes, Rosalind Franklin, Lise Meitner, nuclear fission, DNA structure

Lise Meitner and Rosalind Franklin: The Nobel Prize as a Gauge for Female Scientific Achievement
An analysis of the Nobel Prize system and its current male prejudices resulting from the awarding process and other societal factors. This analysis uses the lives of Rosalind Franklind and Lise Meitner as case studies.
